syntax: document.createDocumentFragment()

Use: this is usfule for extract elements from document, and manipulate the elements, and then append it back.

Tip:
  1. node is append to documentfragment will be removed from the document file
 
        <ul>
          <li> first </li>
          <li> second </li>
          <li> thrid <li>
         </ul>
         
         var fragment = document.createDocumentFragment();
         fragment.appendchild(document.querySelecor("ul li"));
         after appendChild() execute, the first li element will be removed.
         
         <ul>
          <li> second </li>
          <li> thrid <li>
         </ul>
  
  2. when you append framgment to document, only its content will be appended to the target
  
  3. after you manipulate with childnodes, children methods , you can put it back
  
  
  
  
  
